---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Group Scout" description="What Group Scout is, the problem it solves, and how it works">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 mb-8">About Group Scout</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-zinc dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        Group Scout is a Go-based pipeline that monitors public data sources for hotel group sales
        leads — construction projects, contract awards, film productions, sports events — and
        surfaces actionable intelligence to a hotel sales team via Slack.
      </p>

      <p>
        The problem it solves: hotel group sales requires proactive outreach, not inbound waiting.
        The signals that predict large room blocks exist in public data — building permits, contract
        awards, permit filings — but they’re scattered, inconsistent, and slow to connect manually.
        Group Scout automates the collection, deduplication, enrichment, and delivery.
      </p>

      <p>
        The stack: Go backend with a Postgres datastore, Claude for structured enrichment and lead
        scoring, and a Slack Block Kit digest as the delivery layer. Data sources include municipal
        building permits and contract award filings. The pipeline runs on a schedule and posts only
        net-new leads above a configurable value threshold.
      </p>

      <p>
        This site has two blogs. The <a href="/blog/">build log</a> traces the product journey —
        decisions made, things that didn’t work, and the domain knowledge picked up along the way.
        The <a href="/engineering/">engineering notes</a> go deeper on technical implementation:
        architecture, data models, Go patterns, and LLM integration design.
      </p>

      <p>
        The source is at <a href="https://github.com/alvindcastro/groupscout">github.com/alvindcastro/groupscout</a>.
        For the person behind it, visit <a href="https://alvindcastro.github.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">alvindcastro.github.io</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
